      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Test conditions span the range of clinically relevant loading scenarios including at least two load levels and two construct configurations.",
      "rationale": "Testing was conducted under a single ASTM F1717 standard test configuration (compression-bending, 10° offset). Only one load level and one construct configuration were evaluated, which does not fully span the clinical loading space. This factor is assessed below the required level. The shortfall is acknowledged and accepted given that the COU is explicitly scoped to the single ASTM F1717 test condition and medium model influence classification. Achieved level (2) is below required level (3); this is a known gap documented in the decision record."
    },
    {
