      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "FEA model inputs (geometry, material properties, boundary conditions) are demonstrably equivalent to the physical test article inputs within stated tolerances.",
      "rationale": "A formal input equivalency assessment was performed comparing FEA model inputs to measured test article parameters. Geometric equivalency was confirmed within ±0.05 mm by CMM. Material property equivalency was confirmed by lot-specific coupon testing. Boundary conditions in the FEA model replicate the ASTM F1717 fixture constraints as verified by fixture geometry measurements. All input parameters were within stated equivalency tolerances. Achieved level equals required level."
    },
