      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs (stiffness, yield force, force at 40 mm) are directly relevant to the clinical performance and regulatory decision for the pedicle screw construct.",
      "rationale": "Construct stiffness, yield force, and force at 40 mm displacement are the three QoIs specified in ASTM F1717 and are directly relevant to the regulatory submission decision. These QoIs are mechanistically linked to clinical failure modes (fatigue fracture, construct loosening). The QoIs are well-established in the regulatory context for pedicle screw systems. Achieved level equals required level."
    },
